Kim Jong Il Sends Educational Aid Fund and Stipends to Children of Koreans in Japan 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il sent 205 million yen as educational aid fund and stipends to the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) for the democratic national education of the children of Koreans in Japan on the occasion of the 96th birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This remittance brought the total amount of the educational aid fund and stipends sent by Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il to Chongryon in 154 installments for the above-said purpose up to this date to 46,211,223,000 yen.

Order and Medal Commemorating Diamond Jubilee of DPRK Instituted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA)--The Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK on April 10 promulgated a decree on instituting the Order and Medal Commemorating the 6Oth Anniversary of the Founding of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The decree said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will greet before long the 60th anniversary of the founding of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, our glorious country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is the great country of the people, an invincible socialist power, based on the Juche idea and a banner of the national dignity of the sovereign country and its grandeur and prosperity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 President Kim Il Sung's founding of the DPRK on September 9, Juche 37 (1948) marked a historic event which put forward the Korean people as an independent and mighty revolutionary people and ushered in a new era of building a socialist state centered on the popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 60 year-long history of the DPRK represents a history of great changes in which it emerged a powerful state, independent, self-supporting and self-reliant in defence, recording a heroic epic of creation and construction under the guidance of the party and the leader and a sacred path along which it has powerfully demonstrated the advantages and invincibility of socialism of Korean style despite the stern tempest of the anti-imperialist struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Il Sung built new socialist Korea by embodying the idea of believing in people as in Heaven for the first time in the nation's history spanning 5,000 years and laid an eternal foundation for the prosperity of the country and the nation by working heart and soul all his life. These imperishable exploits will shine for all ages. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It is the immense honor and pride for the army and people to celebrate the 60th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK in the stirring period when the nation's dignity and power have been put on the highest level and they greeted the golden days of great prosperity unprecedented in the nation's history thanks to the great Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly makes the following decision to eternally celebrate the six decades shining with victory and glory covered by the DPRK: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
1. The Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly institutes the Order and Medal Commemorating the 60th Anniversary of the Founding of the DPRK&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
2.  It approves the regulations on awarding the order and medal and their explanatory diagram.

Torch Relay for 29th Olympic Games Supported 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Olympic Committee of the DPRK gave the following answer to a question put by KCNA in connection with the torch relay for the 29th Olympic Games: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The torch relays for the 29th Olympic Games to be held in China in August this year are now underway amid the support and welcome from sportspersons and other people of various countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 However, there occurred incidents of creating difficulties in the way of events in some countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Olympic Committee of the DPRK positively supports the above-said torch relays taking place in line with the Olympic idea of peace and friendship and vehemently condemns some disruptive forces' obstructions as a challenge to the Olympic idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is our belief that the international community including the International Olympic Committee will conduct the above-mentioned torch relay in the Olympic idea and spirit as planned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Olympic Committee of the DPRK is now pushing ahead at a final phase with all preparations for successfully ensuring the torch relay slated to take place in Pyongyang on April 28 in close touch with the Organizing Committee of the 29th Olympiad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This event will take place in the most secure and smooth manner as planned in the DPRK where all the people have formed a big harmonious family, single-mindedly united around the WPK, a great party.

Negotiated Solution of Nuclear Issue Urged 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- It is the consistent stand of the DPRK to seek a peaceful negotiated settlement of the nuclear issue and its ultimate goal is to realize the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A DPRK delegate said this in a speech made at the annual meeting of the United Nations Disarmament Commission on April 8. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that now a very tense situation is prevailing on the Korean Peninsula due to the reckless moves of the anti-DPRK, anti-reunification forces at home and abroad, he added these acts cannot but be a very regretful development as they are aimed at bringing back the positive situation in the region favorable for reconciliation and cooperation to the phase of confrontation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that the DPRK government has made patient efforts for the peaceful solution to the nuclear issue but the U.S. has not yet taken any measures to cross the DPRK off the list of sponsors of terrorism and stop applying the trading with the enemy act to it, the commitments the U.S. should fulfill on the principle of action for action. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. sincerely wishes the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula, it should not throw hurdles in the way of settling the nuclear issue with such hostile actions as joint military exercises with south Korea but show its will to unroll its hostile policy towards the DPRK in practice as it committed itself to do so, he declared. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean authorities should stop heading for the anachronistic confrontation with the DPRK, being subservient to outside forces, but behave themselves as required by the historic June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration, he urged. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Holding that this meeting should mark an occasion in realizing the strong desire of humankind for a nuclear-free world, he urged the nuclear weapons states, the U.S. having the world's biggest nuclear arsenal, in particular, to commit themselves to take substantial measures for nuclear arms reduction aimed at the complete elimination of nuclear weapons and thus contribute to attaining the objective of the meeting.

Large Floral Basket Presented to DPRK Embassy in Phnom Penh 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- King of Cambodia Norodom Sihamoni sent a large floral basket to the DPRK embassy in Phnom Penh on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Upon the authorization of the Cambodian king a delegation of the Ministry of the Royal Palace of the Cambodian government headed by Kong Sam Ol, deputy prime minister in charge of Affairs of the Royal Palace, visited the DPRK embassy on April 10 to lay the floral basket before the portraits of President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il.

Large Floral Basket to DPRK Embassy from Great King of Cambodia 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- Norodom Sihanouk, Great king of Cambodia, sent a large floral basket to the DPRK embassy in Phnom Penh on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Upon the authorization of the great king of Cambodia, a delegation of the Ministry of Royal Palace of the Cambodian government headed by Kong Sam Ol, deputy prime minister in charge of Affairs of the Royal Palace, visited the DPRK embassy on April 10 to lay the floral basket before the portraits of President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il.

Congratulations to President of Montenegro 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, on Friday sent a congratulatory message to Filip Vujanovic upon his reelection as President of Montenegro. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim in his message wished the president of Montenegro success in his responsible work for the stability and development of the country.

Premieres of 1st National Art Festival Given 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang April 12 (KCNA) -- Premieres of the first national art festival commemorating the Day of the Sun were given at 12 theatres in Pyongyang on Friday drawing capacity audiences. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the performers were winners of international and national concours, people's actors and actresses, merited actors and actresses, artistes of national and local art organizations, overseas Korean artistes, members of itinerant art squads and working people's art groups. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those of the Women's Band of the Ministry of People's Security performed at the East Pyongyang Grand Theatre, those of the Orchestra of Yun I Sang Music Institute and art troupes of the South Hamgyong, Jagang and Ryanggang provinces at the Yun I Sang Concert Hall, winners of individual contest for "February 16 Art Prize" at the Music Hall of Pyongyang Kim Won Gyun Conservatory and those of the Art Troupe of the South Hwanghae Province at the Pyongyang International Cinema House. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers in their numbers sang high praises of the immortal revolutionary exploits performed by President Kim Il Sung and his noble personality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The art troupe of Koreans in Japan performed at the Pyongyang Grand Theatre and art troupes of Koreans in China and the International United Confederation of Koreans at the Central Youth Hall. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They staged songs and dances and other numbers truthfully representing the strong yearning for the President who made a new history of the Juche-oriented overseas compatriot movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The National Youth Art Squad and the Art Squad of the Pyongyang Guidance Bureau for Construction gave their performances at the Central Youth Hall. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  One-act plays "Under One Roof" and "Choice" were put on the stage at the State Theatrical Theater by artistes of the State Theatrical Company. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pyongyang Circus presented skating acrobatics "The Songun Era Is Good", magic "Rich Catfish Cultivation", physical acrobatics "Double Swing" and other colorful numbers at the Pyongyang Circus Theatre. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Members of itinerant art squads and working people's art groups of different units across the country gave their performances at the People's Palace of Culture, the Central Workers' Hall and the Hall of Culture of the Ministry of Railways. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the audiences were officials of ministries and national institutions, members of the organizing committee of the festival, working people in the city, youth and students, foreign guests and overseas Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Art performances go on.

Performances of 1st National Art Festival Go on
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang April 13 (KCNA) -- Performances of the first national art festival commemorating the Day of the Sun are going on at theatres here, drawing capacity audiences. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Put on the stages were colorful numbers making truthful artistic representation of the people's profound reverence for President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Female solo "Song Devoted to Comrade Kim Jong Il", violin concert of famous work "Azalea" and other numbers sang high praises of the immortal exploits performed by Kim Jong Il, illustrious commander of Mt. Paektu, and fully reflected the fixed faith and will of all servicepersons and people to uphold his leadership with loyalty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Put on the stages were numbers dealing with the happy life of the Korean people in the daily thriving socialist country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pyongyang Circus presented physical acrobatics "Double Swing", skating acrobatics "Rope Jumping" and comic acrobatics "Two Friends," greatly delighting the spectators with complicated and thrilling movements and humorous acting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performances were enjoyed by working people and youth and students in the city, foreign guests and overseas Koreans.

Homage Paid to Kim Il Sung
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- Homage was paid to President Kim Il Sung by artistes of national and local art organizations, overseas Korean artistes, members of itinerant art squads and working people's art groups who are participating in the first national art festival commemorating the Day of the Sun when they visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants in the festival made a bow in humble reverence to the President who devoted his all life for the prosperity of the country and the happiness of the people and laid an eternal foundation for the brilliant development of Juche-based literature and arts.

National Students Basketball Games Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- The national students basketball games took place in Phyongsong, South Phyongan Province between April 5 and 12 to commemorate the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The games brought together at least 20 organizations which were divided into university and college groups. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Male and female players of Kim Il Sung University placed first in the matches of the university group. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Male players of Chongjin College of Information Technology and female players of Pyongyang College of Statistics came first respectively in the matches of the college group.

New Documentary Screened
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- Documentary film "Father of All Families of Country" was screened at the People's Palace of Culture Saturday on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The film deals with the history of great loving care shown by President Kim Il Sung who worked heart and soul to enable the people to lead a more affluent and happier life, considering it as his maxim to believe in people as in Heaven. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also contains impressive scenes showing the true picture of immense happiness and the single-minded unity of the Korean people who have formed a big family holding the President in high esteem as their real father. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The film was watched by senior party and state officials, a chairperson of a friendly party, officials of ministries and national institutions and working people in Pyongyang.

Reception Given by Cuban Ambassador
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- Jose Manuel Galego Montano, Cuban ambassador to the DPRK, hosted a reception at his embassy on Friday on the occasion of the Day of the Sun and the 15th anniversary of General Secretary Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, Ri Ryong Nam, minister of Foreign Trade, Kim Yong Jin, minister of Education, Ri Yong Chol, first secretary of the Central Committee of the youth league, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jose Manuel Galego Montano said at the reception that President    Kim Il Sung liberated Korea through the hard-fought struggle after embarking upon the road of revolution in his early years and built a country of Juche on this land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President is always alive in the hearts of the progressive mankind as he performed great feats as the leader of the heroic Korean people and devoted his all to the struggle for building an independent and developed, socialist country, the ambassador stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that Kim Jong Il is wisely leading the Korean revolution with Songun, he expressed belief that under his wise leadership the Korean people will surely win in the struggle with the imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Yang Hyong Sop in his speech said it is an expression of the Cuban party, government and people's trust in Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and an encouragement to the army and people of the DPRK that Cuban comrades have joined the Korean people in commemorating the significant holidays of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The undying feats performed by Kim Il Sung for the country and people, the times and history and his cause are successfully being defended and carried forward to completion by Kim Jong Il, he said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We hope that the government and people of Cuba will steadily register great success in the work to decisively smash the U.S. vicious move for isolating and suffocating Cuba and defend, consolidate and develop their socialist gains under the wise leadership of respected Fidel Castro and Raul Castro, he said.

Vietnamese Embassy Officials Visit Mangyongdae
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- Ambassador Le Van Cu and staff members of the Vietnamese embassy here visited Mangyongdae on Saturday on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The guests laid a floral basket at the old home of President Kim Il Sung in Mangyongdae. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then they looked round the relics there, being briefed on the fact that the President was born in the house with low straw-thatched roof, fostered his high ambition to liberate the country in his childhood and embarked on the road of revolution in his early years and on the careers of members of the patriotic and revolutionary Mangyongdae family. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They planted a tree around the old home.

Book and Photo Exhibition and Film Show for Foreign Students
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- A book and photo exhibition and a film show for foreign students studying at Kim Il Sung University were held at the Pyongyang Cultural Exhibition Saturday on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The foreign students went round photos showing the undying feats performed by President Kim Il Sung in turning Korea into a socialist power, independent in politics, self-supporting in economy and self-reliant in national defence, and those of General Secretary Kim Jong Il traveling a ceaseless journey for the Songun revolutionary leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also looked round famous works authored by Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and books introducing politics, economy, culture, history, etc. of the DPRK before watching Korean documentary "They Were Always Together on the Road to Bring About the People's Well-being".

Film Show Given for Chinese Residents in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- A film show was arranged by the Pyongyang City People's Committee for Chinese residents in Pyongyang at the Taedonggang Club for the Diplomatic Corps on Saturday on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were officials of the Central Committee of the Federation of Chinese Residents in the DPRK including its vice-chairman and Chinese residents in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were officials of the Pyongyang City People's Committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants watched the Korean documentary film "They Were Always Together on the Road to Bring About the People's Well-being".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was followed by a singing gathering of Chinese residents to commemorate the Day of the Sun.

Delegations of Overseas Koreans and Foreigners Here
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- A delegation of Koreans in Japan led by Ri Ki Sok, vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan, a delegation of the Federation of Koreans in Canada led by its Chairman Kim Su Hae, a delegation of the Federation of Koreans in the U.S. led by its Chairman Yun Kil Sang, a delegation of the Federation of Koreans in New Zealand led by its Chairman Jang Yun Guk and a delegation of the Federation of Koreans in Australia led by its Vice-Chairman Kim Hyon Bong and Choe Kon Guk, Korean residing in Germany, arrived here on Saturday on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The arrivals on the same day included a delegation of the Russian International Charity Fund "Protectors of Art for the Century" led by its President Oleg Oleinik, Secretary General of the International Institute of the Juche Idea Kenichi Ogami and his party, a delegation of the Bangladesh Self-Reliance Research Centre led by its General Secretary Jobaida Pervin, W. A. Duminduwardane, vice-chairman of the Committee of Self-Reliance Studies in Sri Lanka, a delegation of the Group for the Study of the Juche Idea of Kyrgyzstan led by its Chief Anarbek Usupbaev, a delegation of the French Group for the Study of the Juche Idea led by Lyne Sinyodyium, Noboru Kameda, representative of the Society of the Japan-Korea Culture, and Takashi Nada, representative of the Ehime Institute for Contemporary Korean Issue in Japan.

DPRK Proves Successful at Asian Taekwon-Do Championships
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- Players of the DPRK proved successful at the 4th Asian Taekwon-Do Championships held in Kazakhstan from April 2 to 6. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK bagged 24 gold, two silver and six bronze medals at the championships to come first in the total standings of countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its players took the first place in the adult men's and women's team standings, the men's and women's team pattern competitions and the women's team sparring matches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the adult group, Yun Chung Nam, Pu Song Jin and Mun Hyok picked up gold medals in men's patterns individual, Ri Chol Ok in women's pattern individual, exhibition for special skills and over 75kg sparring matches, An Yun Mi in women's pattern individual and 63kg sparring, O Kum Ju in women's pattern individual and 75kg sparring, Sin Jong Hwa in women's self-defence martial art and 69kg sparring individual and Kim Chol, Ji Chol Guk and Pak Yong Bom respectively in men's 50kg, 57kg and 78kg sparring individual and Paek Un Hyang in  women's 57kg sparring individual. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the junior group Pak Chol took the men's pattern individual and 57kg sparring and Ri Hyang Mi the women's pattern individual, exhibition for special skills and 58kg sparring.

Reception Given for Russian Delegation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- The Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries gave a reception at Pyongyang Koryo Hotel Saturday for the visiting delegation of the Russian International Charity Fund "Protectors of Arts for the Century".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were members of the delegation led by Oleg Oleinik, president of the fund, and Ambassador Valery Sukhinin and staff members of the Russian embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Hong Son Ok, vice-chairperson of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries and chairperson of the DPRK-Russia Friendship Association, and others and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the reception.

Title of Generalissimo Associated with Boundless Reverence
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il Sung was awarded the title of Generalissimo of the DPRK on April 13, Juche 81 (1992). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The title is permeated with heartfelt reverence of the servicepersons and people for the brilliant commander of Mt. Paektu who founded the heroic Korean People's Army, revolutionary armed forces, and defeated two imperialisms with his outstanding military ability in one generation to defend the dignity and sovereignty of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President was handed over two pistols carrying the lofty patriotic will from his father Kim Hyong Jik in his early years. He, giving priority to arms, dedicated his whole life to the struggle for the freedom and liberation of the country and to the happiness of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He applied strategy, tactics and guerrilla war methods unprecedented in the history to the war against Japanese imperialism. They are still shining as miracle in the world military history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK under the guidance of the brilliant commander also wrought a military miracle in the 1950s. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He with his unique war tactics shattered into smithereens "the myth of mightiness" of U.S. imperialism which started the war to stamp out the young DPRK, thus striking the military experts of the world with admiration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the efforts for defending socialism for scores of years, too, he brought the U.S. imperialists to their knees and safeguarded the destiny of the country and the nation without a gun report. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 President Kim Il Sung was the genius of military who created Juche-oriented military ideology, strategy, tactics and war methods, the legendary great man who won victory after victory and the iron-willed brilliant commander who adorned his great life with unheard-of miracles. In praise of his exploits, the Korean servicepersons and people conferred the title of Generalissimo on him on the occasion of his 80th birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This was an appreciation by the history, the will of the nation and the demand of the times.

Books on Feats of President Widely Read
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- The habit of reading is being given to fuller play in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea these days with the approach of the significant Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
One can see working people and school youth and children who are engrossed in reading "With the Century", reminiscences of President Kim Il Sung and books on his revolutionary history with ardent yearning for him everywhere in streets, villages and parks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Among the books are "Dawn of Revolution", "Bright Morning", "Spring of Guerrilla Base" and "Earth Turns Green" out of the series "Immortal History".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The novel "Dawn of Revolution" reflects historic facts that the President brought about the dawn of the Korean revolution by believing in the might of popular masses and rallying them towards the end of the 1920s. The novel "Bright Morning" deals with the noble popular traits of the President who united in one ideology and will the people of all strata with checked careers with his philosophy of truth in and love for the people after the liberation of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The novels "Spring of Guerrilla Base" and "Earth Turns Green" also show with deep impression the revolutionary history of the President who led the grave Korean revolution along the one road of victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The novels "Thawing of Snow" and "Prelude to Spring" also deal with the undying feats performed by the President for the times and people. Through the books, the readers get deep knowledge on the greatness and immortal exploits of the President who won back the ruined nation, established the Juche-based socialist Korea in this land and devoted his whole life for the country and people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Reading with deep emotion a collection of short stories newly published in commemoration of the 100th birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung, they harden their faith and will to hold the President in high esteem forever and accomplish without fail the revolutionary cause of Juche pioneered in Mt. Paektu under the Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il.

Full Display of Revolutionary Spirit of Mt. Paektu Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- The revolutionary spirit of Mt. Paektu, created during the protracted and hard-fought anti-Japanese struggle, is a source of all the miracles wrought by the DPRK in the present times and it is a symbol of heroism displayed by the Korean army and people, says Rodong Sinmun in an editorial article Saturday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With this great spirit the army and people of the DPRK defeated two imperialist formidable enemies and built a powerful socialist country from scratch, the article says, adding that the victory of the Songun revolution won by the DPRK that brought the dawn of a great prosperous powerful nation after successfully concluding the "Arduous March" precisely means the victory by the above-said spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean army and people's ideological and moral mainstay is the revolutionary spirit of Mt. Paektu that was created under the leadership of President Kim Il Sung during the grim anti-Japanese war, it notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This spirit represents absolute and unconditional loyalty to the leader, the spirit of self-reliance and fortitude and the indefatigable fighting spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary soldier spirit displayed by the Korean People's Army, the revolutionary spirit symbolizing and representing the Songun era, is a successful succession to the revolutionary spirit of Mt. Paektu, and signal creation and change being wrought in the country are a precious fruition of this spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary spirit of Mt. Paektu serves as a solid cornerstone of our army and people's transparent faith in independence and their high national pride. It also serves as an inexhaustible source of strong disposition of the Korean army and people who know nothing impossible. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is great spirit that helps the Korean army and people train themselves to be indomitable fighters and live and struggle with matchless courage and pluck with nothing to be afraid of in the world. It is also the bottom of their steadfast working-class stand against imperialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the unshakable creed of General Secretary Kim Jong Il that there would be no spirit of Korea, the soul of its nation, to say nothing of the victory of the revolution, without the revolutionary spirit of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today it is a social trait of the DPRK that all the people learn from the noble fighting spirit displayed by the anti-Japanese revolutionary forerunners. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary spirit of Mt. Paektu will encourage the Korean army and people to perform fresh heroic feats, fully displaying its inexhaustible might with passage of time as there is Kim Jong Il who is faithfully inheriting and eternally glorifying the revolutionary traditions created by the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the steadfast will of our army and people to accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche under the leadership of Kim Jong Il to the end, considering the said spirit as an eternal treasured sword. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean revolution was started and has victoriously advanced with arms. There can never be change in the truth of history that arms guarantee the victory of socialism and the independent dignity and prosperity of each country and nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The path of Juche opened up by the President is that of eternal victory and prosperity, and the revolutionary spirit of Mt. Paektu is the noblest revolutionary spirit that our army and people should fully display in their long journey of struggle. The Korean revolution will always emerge victorious as there are the seasoned and tested guidance of the great Workers' Party of Korea and the single-minded unity and inexhaustible mental power of all servicepersons and people.

Memorial Service Held in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- A memorial service was held in Seoul on April 8 for the victims of the "case of the People's Revolutionary Party" under the sponsorship of the Society for Commemorating Participants in the Democratic Movement and others in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the memorial service were figures of different circles including O Jong Ryol, co-chairman of the Solidarity for Progress of south Korea, and Ro Jung Son, co-representative of the April Revolution Society, those related to the case and bereaved families of the victims. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers there noted that 33 years have passed since the pro-reunification patriots were killed after being branded as prime movers in the "case of the People's Revolutionary Party" and that the problem has not been settled yet though they were declared not guilty at the court. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that with the emergence of the present "government" the south Korean society is getting more conservative, they stressed that it presents itself as an urgent issue to inherit the spirit of the martyrs who devoted their lives to reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They underscored the need to fully probe the truth behind the "case" in order to prevent the repetition of such grievous deaths. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They demanded the "government" immediately abolish the "National Security Law" and opt to work for achieving the reunification of the country, the hope of all the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A video on the theme "They are born to be flowers for reunification and peace" was shown at the memorial service.

South Korea-U.S. Security Meeting under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- The People for Achieving Peace and Reunification, the South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification and the Association for Supporting Prisoners of Conscience of the Family Movement for Realizing Democracy in south Korea jointly called a press conference in Seoul on April 8 to denounce the south Korea-U.S. "meeting on security policy initiative." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers there referred to the fact that the 17th "meeting on security policy initiative" opened in Seoul that day. They held that what is a matter of concern is that the Lee Myung Bak regime intends to fully meet the U.S. demands for increasing south Korea's share of the upkeep of the U.S. forces in south Korea incurred by the expenses for the transfer of the Second Division of the U.S. forces in south Korea and the participation in the missile defense system  (MD) and the PSI. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A press release read out there accused the U.S. of behaving arbitrarily, blustering that the expenses for the transfer of the Second Division of the U.S. forces in south Korea should be covered with south Korea's share of the upkeep of the U.S. forces in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
